OFFSITE VENUE RESEARCH
=====================
Prepared for: 2026 Leadership Retreat Planning
Date: November 2025

EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
-----------------
This document evaluates potential venues for the annual 2-day
leadership retreat planned for Q2 2026. Budget: $15,000-25,000.

NOTE: This research is for the ANNUAL RETREAT (multi-day event),
not for regular leadership offsite meetings which are typically
held on-site in our conference rooms.

---

VENUE OPTION 1: Cavallo Point Lodge
Location: Sausalito, CA (25 min from office)
Capacity: Up to 20 in meeting space
Overnight Rooms: Yes (30 rooms available)
Meeting Space: Harbor View Room
Catering: On-site restaurant, excellent
AV: Full setup included
Cost Estimate: $18,000 for 2 days + 1 night
Pros: Stunning views, close to office, great food
Cons: Can be foggy, limited availability in spring

---

VENUE OPTION 2: Carneros Resort
Location: Napa Valley (1 hour from office)
Capacity: Up to 25 in meeting space
Overnight Rooms: Yes (cottage style)
Meeting Space: The Vintner's Room
Catering: Farm-to-table restaurant
AV: Available for additional fee ($500)
Cost Estimate: $22,000 for 2 days + 1 night
Pros: Wine country setting, private cottages, relaxing
Cons: Farther from office, premium pricing

---

VENUE OPTION 3: Claremont Club & Spa
Location: Berkeley Hills (30 min from office)
Capacity: Up to 30 in meeting space
Overnight Rooms: Yes (hotel rooms)
Meeting Space: Multiple options
Catering: Multiple on-site restaurants
AV: Full setup included
Cost Estimate: $16,000 for 2 days + 1 night
Pros: Spa amenities for team building, views, historic
Cons: Can feel corporate/conference-y

---

VENUE OPTION 4: Hotel Drisco
Location: Pacific Heights, SF (15 min from office)
Capacity: Up to 15 in meeting space (smaller)
Overnight Rooms: Yes (boutique)
Meeting Space: Library Room
Catering: Continental breakfast included
AV: Basic setup only
Cost Estimate: $12,000 for 2 days + 1 night
Pros: Intimate setting, walkable neighborhood
Cons: Limited meeting space, no dedicated AV

---

RECOMMENDATION
--------------
For the annual leadership retreat, recommend Cavallo Point for
the best balance of location, amenities, and value.

